Text:
Princess Alexia descends a dark staircase with a magic
lamp in hand.

My sister said she was grateful for the information.
She hopes you will continue to cooperate with us.
I'm honored.

I think we should assume that Perv Asshat has ties
with the Cult.

Agreed. I believe a little digging into his dubious
background will confirm it beyond a doubt.
The only problem is we don't have any proof.

Very true. This is an issue involving both government
and religion, so normal evidence won't be enough.

I know that. Even my father was unusually forceful
about the matter...

He said that if we're planning to link the Cult of
Diablos with the Church, then we're going to need
an explanation that the citizenry and neighboring
nations will find convincing.

Being branded as heretics would certainly be an
unpleasant outcome.

Yeah, and Father is very adamant about not stirring
up trouble with the Church...

How the hell does he think he's going to resolve all
the strife caused by the Cult?
Perhaps he intends to leave things as they have been.
As they have been...?

Just an errant conjecture. Please forget I said
anything.
...Well, we can set that aside for now.

I'm more concerned about something my sister told me.
She said that King Oriana seemed kind of vacant during
their audience with the monarch.

Apparently he wasn't his usual self, like maybe his
mind was elsewhere because of his daughter's crime.
She also mentioned he smelled slightly sweet.
*gasp*

A sweet smell... Beta knows of a certain drug with the
same properties.
We may already be too late...
The Cult is always on the move.

With the way my father does things, this land may 
fall prey to them soon, too...
By the way...
Where do these stairs lead?

To one of the entrances to the tunnels beneath the
city. But surely you already know that?

Yes... You speak of the underground labyrinth beneath
the capital, which is said to have been constructed long,
long ago as a means of escape for the royal family.

Labyrinth... Yeah, that sounds about right. Any
maps, keys, or ciphers that existed have all been
lost, so now it's nothing more than a giant maze.
So...why are we headed there now?
So I can murder you.

...Just kidding. Though it doesn't look like you were
scared in the slightest.
Eek, don't kill me...!

It's possible that Rose ran down here. That's why
we're going to have a look.
Um, please wait a moment.
What is it?
Have you told anyone else about this?
Why would I? They'd only try to stop us.
You said that this is a maze.
Are you sure we can find our way back out?
We'll just go back the way we came.

Um, would you mind not dragging me into every flight
of fancy you have?
If you have any complaints, feel free to leave.

Beta considers heading back without her for a
moment, but it wouldn't do to have Alexia die
just yet.
Keeping her safe is part of the job, Beta.
With a small sigh, she follows Alexia down.
